# Appdoers Hub Project Mapping

When creating a ticket, use the client and project from the active Hub session. Never hardcode project UUIDs.

## Always confirm live

1. Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs list-clients`
2. Run `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs list-projects --client-id "<client-uuid>"`
3. Ask the user to confirm client + project (match **both** `company_name` and project `name`)
4. Save with `set-session`

## Directory hints (confirm with user via session)

These are shortcuts only — always verify via `list-clients` / `list-projects`:

- `Appdoers CRM/` → usually Appdoers / Business Setup & Launch
- `AppdoersWebsite/` → usually Appdoers / New Website
- `ABCWebsite/` → usually Ashburton Baptist Church / New Website
- Other folders → ask user, then `set-session`

## Selection rules

- Match **both** project name and `client_name` — never pick a project id from name alone
- After creating or listing tickets, confirm `client_name` in the response matches the intended client
- If a ticket is on the wrong project/client, fix with `update-ticket --project-id "<correct-uuid>" --note "Reassigned to correct client/project"`
- If mapping is unclear, ask the user — do not default silently
